defaultPHE’s Knowledge and Intelligence Servicedefault&#xa0;defaultOn 1 April 2013 the regi
defaultonal Public Health Observatories (PHOs) transferred along with the specialist observatories and the National Cancer Intelligence Network into PHE as a single Knowledge and Intelligence service for England.
default&#xa0;
defaultThe historical role of the PHOs remains fundament
defaultally unchanged and is now carried out by PHE’s eight Knowledge and Intelligence Teams.  We are building on the highly regarded work of our predecessor organisations to ensure we have a knowledge service to ensure decisions we make about health are based on
default the best information and evidence available and allow us to secure the best possible
default outcome.
default&#xa0;
defaultPHE continues to produce a range of interactive resources, reports and profiling tools to help local government and the health service understand health need, make comparisons with other areas and make informed 
defaultd
defaultecisions.  A flavour of our work is given by
default the brief description of some of our key products set out in Annex A.
